data.title: US presidential vote count continues, Trump wins swing state
data.description: WASHINGTON — Democratic candidate Kamala Harris and her Republican opponent Donald Trump on Tuesday picked up early wins in their respective strongholds as vote counting for one of the most consequential presidential elections in United States history continued.

data.title: Philippines approves purchase of 40 patrol boats amid China spat
data.description: MANILA — The Philippines has approved the purchase of 40 fast patrol craft worth 25.8 billion pesos (US$441 million), seeking to bolster maritime security as tensions with Beijing in the South China Sea linger.

data.title: Results of national exit poll on US presidential election
data.description: NEW YORK - Democrat Kamala Harris faced Republican Donald Trump on Tuesday in the United States presidential election, after the two candidates vied for support by staking positions on issues including abortion, the economy and foreign policy.

data.title: Hoax bomb threats linked to Russia target polling places in battleground states, FBI says
data.description: ATLANTA: Hoax bomb threats, many of which appeared to originate from Russian email domains, were directed at polling locations in three battleground states - Georgia, Michigan and Wisconsin - as Election Day voting was underway, the FBI said on Tuesday.

data.title: US expects foreign adversaries to stoke anger over election results
data.description: WASHINGTON — Russia continued to push out disinformation to undermine faith in the United States election Tuesday, but American officials said they were bracing for an even bigger assault of false narratives in the days and weeks after the vote.

data.title: Myanmar junta leader makes first visit to China
data.description: The leader of Myanmar’s military junta visited China on Tuesday to join regional meetings in Kunming, the capital of southwestern Yunnan Province, state television reported.

data.title: ‘Nazi takeover’ plotters arrested in Germany
data.description: Eight men suspected of plotting to install a Nazi regime in eastern states of Germany were arrested amid a massive police operation early Tuesday.

data.title: Sweden sentences Koran-burner to jail
data.description: STOCKHOLM - A Swedish court on Tuesday found a far-right activist guilty of two counts of hate crime against Muslims over statements he made while burning copies of the Koran, acts that triggered riots in the country in 2022.

data.title: Indonesia evacuating 16,000 as volcano erupts again
data.description: JAKARTA - The Indonesian government aims to evacuate at least 16,000 residents from villages around the active Mount Lewotobi Laki-laki volcano that erupted and killed nine people and damaged thousands of houses, an official said on Tuesday.

data.title: UK proposes ‘historic’ anti-smoking law
data.description: LONDON - The British government has introduced a new bill aimed at creating the first “smoke-free generation”, as part of a plan to ease pressure on the National Health Service.

data.title: Births in Japan fall another 6% in first half
data.description: TOKYO - The number of babies born to Japanese nationals in Japan fell 6.3% in the first half of this year from a year earlier to 329,998, government data showed on Tuesday, as the number of marriages continues to decline amid shifting values.

data.title: Podcaster Joe Rogan endorses Donald Trump for US president
data.description: WASHINGTON - Popular podcaster Joe Rogan, who recently interviewed Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump for nearly three hours, said on Monday he has endorsed the former president in the race to the White House.

data.title: Philippines braces for another typhoon after storms swamp crops
data.description: MANILA — The Philippines is set to be drenched by its fourth storm in just over a month, which threatens to add to a growing tally of crop losses that total at least 11.5 billion pesos (US$197 million) this year.
